### Important SQL Concepts Understood
- WHERE executes before GROUP BY
- HAVING executes after aggregation
- SELECT aliases are not available inside HAVING
- ORDER BY can often use aliases because it executes later
- GROUP BY creates separate groups based on repeated values
- Aggregate functions work within groups
- SQL problems can be solved in multiple valid ways

